  "prompt": "I have given class 10 exam in 2014 ,and I am giving 12 exam in 2017 .am I eligible for JEE 2017 as I will appear for 1st time?",
  "response": "For JEE eligibility, you need to fulfill certain criteria related to your year of passing the Class 12 exam and the number of attempts. As per the eligibility criteria for JEE in 2017:\n\n1. **Year of Passing 12th Examination:** Candidates should have passed their Class 12th or equivalent qualifying examination in 2015 or 2016, or they should be appearing for it in 2017.\n\n2. **Number of Attempts:** A candidate is allowed a maximum of three consecutive attempts for JEE Main. Therefore, if 2017 is your first attempt, you would be eligible.\n\n3. **Age Limit:** Generally, candidates whose date of birth falls on or after October 1, 1992, are eligible. However, there is a relaxation of 5 years for SC, ST, and PwD candidates.\n\nAs you mentioned that you are appearing for your Class 12 examination in 2017, this would make you eligible for JEE 2017, assuming you meet the age criteria and have not used up your maximum number of attempts. Always make sure to check the latest information on the official JEE website or official notification for any updates or clarifications.",
